{"id": "adi-adis16480bmlz", "item_name": "10-DOF MEMS inertial measurement unit with on-board sensor fusion", "description": "A 10 degrees-of-freedom MEMS inertial measurement unit that integrates a triaxial gyroscope (±450°/sec dynamic range), a triaxial accelerometer (±10 g), a triaxial magnetometer (±2.5 gauss), and a barometric pressure sensor (300 mbar to 1100 mbar). An on-board extended Kalman filter fuses the sensor data to produce calibrated dynamic orientation outputs (attitude and heading). Each sensor is factory-calibrated for sensitivity, bias, and axial alignment, and the module communicates over a 4-wire SPI digital interface.", "gold_eccn": "7A994", "manufacturer": "Analog Devices", "source_url": "https://www.analog.com/en/support/view-export-classification.html", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "7", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER A (Analog Devices on BIS public list; ECCN human-visible in ADI export tool). Search 'ADIS16480BMLZ' in Product Model Search; read US ECCN column. Confirmed 2026-06-24 via rendered DOM + ADI FetchExportClassificationData JSON. Tool row: \"ADIS16480BMLZ | 10 DoF IMU, with Attitude & Heading | 7A994 | 8542390090\". verified=false pending maintainer sign-off."}
{"id": "adi-adis16545-3bmlz", "item_name": "Precision 6-DOF MEMS IMU, ±2000°/s gyro range", "description": "A precision 6 degrees-of-freedom MEMS inertial measurement unit comprising a triaxial gyroscope configured for a ±2000°/sec full-scale range and a triaxial accelerometer with a ±8 g range. It provides high-stability, low-noise performance with roughly 0.7°/hr gyroscope in-run bias stability and about 3.2 µg accelerometer in-run bias stability, plus factory-calibrated sensitivity, bias, and axial alignment. It outputs triaxial delta-angle and delta-velocity data over a SPI digital interface.", "gold_eccn": "7A003.d.1", "manufacturer": "Analog Devices", "source_url": "https://www.analog.com/en/support/view-export-classification.html", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "7", "difficulty": "hard", "notes": "TIER A (ADI export tool, human-visible). Search 'ADIS16545-3BMLZ'. Tool row: \"ADIS16545-3BMLZ | 6 DOF Prec IMU, 8g (2000 DPS DNR) | 7A003.d.1 | 8542390090\". HARD CASE: only the -3 (2000 DPS) variant steps up to 7A003.d.1; lower-range siblings are 7A994 - dynamic range drives the subparagraph. Confirmed 2026-06-24 (DOM + JSON). verified=false."}
{"id": "adi-adxrs453brgz", "item_name": "±300°/s single-axis MEMS angular rate gyroscope", "description": "A high-performance single-axis (yaw / z-axis) MEMS angular rate sensor with a ±300°/sec measurement range and a 16-bit digital output delivered as part of a 32-bit SPI message. A differential quad-sensor design rejects linear acceleration, giving very low vibration sensitivity (about 0.01°/sec/g) and roughly 16°/hr null bias stability for accurate rate sensing in high-shock, high-vibration environments. It includes internal temperature compensation, operates from 3.3 V to 5 V over -40°C to +105°C, and survives 2000 g powered shock.", "gold_eccn": "7A994", "manufacturer": "Analog Devices", "source_url": "https://www.analog.com/en/support/view-export-classification.html", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "7", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER A (ADI export tool, human-visible). Search 'ADXRS453BRGZ'. Tool row: \"ADXRS453BRGZ | SOIC Digital Output Gyro +/-300 | 7A994 | 8542390090\". Standalone single-axis gyro (sensor-type variety vs the IMUs). Confirmed 2026-06-24 (DOM + JSON). verified=false."}
{"id": "honeywell-hguide-i300", "item_name": "Tactical-grade 6-DOF MEMS inertial measurement unit (~1 cubic inch)", "description": "An industrial/tactical-grade 6 degrees-of-freedom MEMS inertial measurement unit in a roughly 1 cubic inch, ~35 gram, ~0.5 W package, integrating a 3-axis gyroscope and 3-axis accelerometer for low-noise, high-stability inertial sensing in harsh environments. It offers configurable output data rates and RS-422, 5 V TTL, and CAN interfaces.", "gold_eccn": "7A994", "manufacturer": "Honeywell Aerospace", "source_url": "https://www.honeywellaerospace.com/us/en/products-and-services/products/navigation-and-sensors/inertial-measurement-units/hguide-i300-mems-inertial-measurement-unit", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "7", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER B (Honeywell Aerospace, not on BIS list; ECCN human-visible on the manufacturer product page). Quote: \"It has an ECCN of 7A994 and is generally available without an export license.\" Confirmed 2026-06-24. verified=false."}
{"id": "lnd-202-bf3", "item_name": "Boron-trifluoride thermal neutron proportional counter", "description": "A cylindrical BF3-filled proportional counter for thermal-neutron detection, charged with boron-trifluoride gas at 400 torr (21 C) in a 90.45 cm^3 effective volume. It provides a thermal-neutron sensitivity of 2.08 CPS/NV with a maximum plateau slope of 1%/100 V. The aluminum-cathode tube measures 0.93 in (23.62 mm) effective diameter by 12.13 in (308.1 mm) overall length, with an 8.13 in (206.5 mm) active length, and runs at a recommended 1350 V over -50 to +100 C.", "gold_eccn": "1A999", "manufacturer": "LND, Inc.", "source_url": "https://www.lndinc.com/faq/", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "1", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER B (LND not on BIS list; ECCN human-visible on LND FAQ, which assigns ECCN by product family). Quote: \"Our BF3 detectors and B10 lined detectors have been assigned ECCN 1A999 by BIS.\" Specs from product page https://www.lndinc.com/products/neutron-detectors/202/. verified=false."}
{"id": "lnd-2311-b10", "item_name": "Boron-10 lined thermal neutron proportional counter", "description": "A boron-lined proportional counter for thermal-neutron detection using a B-10 coating that is 96% enriched at 0.5 mg/cm^2 thickness, with an argon fill at atmospheric pressure (760 torr, 21 C). Its thermal-neutron sensitivity is 0.25 CPS/NV. The tube measures 0.63 in (16.0 mm) maximum diameter by 2.75 in (69.9 mm) maximum length, with a 1.25 in (31.8 mm) effective length, and operates at a recommended 850 V over -50 to +100 C.", "gold_eccn": "1A999", "manufacturer": "LND, Inc.", "source_url": "https://www.lndinc.com/faq/", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "1", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER B (LND FAQ, human-visible; family-level assignment). Quote: \"Our BF3 detectors and B10 lined detectors have been assigned ECCN 1A999 by BIS.\" Specs from https://www.lndinc.com/products/neutron-detectors/2311/. verified=false."}
{"id": "lnd-2517-he3", "item_name": "Helium-3 thermal neutron detector tube", "description": "A cylindrical proportional counter for detecting thermal neutrons, filled with Helium-3 gas at 4560 torr (21 C). It has a thermal-neutron sensitivity of 1.9 counts per second per unit neutron velocity (CPS/NV) and an effective gas volume of 3.91 cm^3. The tube measures 0.5 in (12.7 mm) overall diameter by 3.7 in (93.98 mm) overall length, with a 1.9 in (48.26 mm) active length, and operates at a recommended 1200 V over -50 to +100 C.", "gold_eccn": "1C232", "manufacturer": "LND, Inc.", "source_url": "https://www.lndinc.com/faq/", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "1", "difficulty": "hard", "notes": "TIER B (LND FAQ, human-visible). Quote: \"Certain models of our 3He tubes are covered by the ECCN 1C232.\" 1C232 controls Helium-3 (nuclear nonproliferation). CAVEAT: FAQ hedges 'certain models' - per-model 1C232 vs EAR99/1A999 not individually published; the He-3 detector is the canonical 1C232 fit. Specs from https://www.lndinc.com/products/neutron-detectors/2517/. verified=false."}
{"id": "oberdorfer-obn9000rs3", "item_name": "Bronze rotary gear pump, 23 GPM", "description": "A pedestal-mounted positive-displacement bronze rotary gear pump for transferring clean lubricating fluids in industrial and marine service. It delivers up to 23 GPM at differential pressures to 150 PSI through 1-inch NPT ports, with a stainless-steel shaft, self-lubricating carbon bearings, and a Viton lip seal. It handles fluids from -40 F to 400 F and is capable of suction lifts up to 20 feet at speeds to 1750 RPM.", "gold_eccn": "2B999.j", "manufacturer": "Oberdorfer (Ingersoll Rand)", "source_url": "https://www.motion.com/products/sku/11016143", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "2", "difficulty": "hard", "notes": "TIER B (distributor Motion Industries; ECCN human-visible in product title). Quote: \"OBN9000RS3 ECCN 2B999.J GEAR PUMP\". 2B999.j = positive-displacement pumps for corrosive service. CAVEAT: ECCN sits in the distributor product-name string (not a dedicated field) and the manufacturer page omits it; value appears consistently across distributors. verified=false."}
{"id": "nachi-7002cydup4", "item_name": "Super-precision angular contact ball bearing, 15 mm bore (P4/ABEC-7)", "description": "A single-row precision angular contact ball bearing in the 7000C series with a 15 mm bore, 32 mm outside diameter, 9 mm width, and a 15-degree contact angle optimized for high speed. It has an open closure and a polyamide cage with steel rings and balls, rated for 6.65 kN dynamic / 3.7 kN static load and a maximum speed of 49500 rpm grease / 68000 rpm oil. It is a P4 (ABEC-7) super-precision class bearing normally mounted in pairs for machine-tool spindle support.", "gold_eccn": "EAR99", "manufacturer": "NACHI", "source_url": "https://www.powelltool.com/products/7002CYDUP4-NAC", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "2", "difficulty": "hard", "notes": "TIER B (distributor Powell Tool Supply; ECCN human-visible). Quote: \"Standards and Approvals: ECCN: EAR99\". TRAP CASE: a genuine P4/ABEC-7 super-precision spindle bearing - the tolerance class 2A001 names - yet correctly EAR99 because its small dimensions fall outside the 2A001 size envelope. Tests over-classification. verified=false."}
{"id": "piper-553-876-camlatch", "item_name": "Aircraft access-panel cam latch (airframe hardware)", "description": "A lightweight cam latch used for access-panel, inspection-panel, and cargo-compartment closure and retention on fixed-wing aircraft, providing secure mechanical latching of airframe panels.", "gold_eccn": "9A991.d", "manufacturer": "Piper Aircraft", "source_url": "https://www.pilotshq.com/products/piper-aircraft-553-876-cam-latch-oem-airframe-hardware-part", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "9", "difficulty": "easy", "notes": "TIER C (distributor PilotsHQ; ECCN human-visible). Quote: \"ECCN: 9A991.d\". 9A991.d is the catch-all for commercial aircraft parts/components. CAVEAT: PilotsHQ ECCNs appear templated to the BIS aircraft-parts default - cross-check vs the OEM before relying. verified=false."}
{"id": "piper-101918-coax-gps", "item_name": "Aircraft GPS antenna coaxial cable assembly", "description": "A coaxial cable assembly for GPS antenna-to-receiver connections in aircraft avionics installations; an RF interconnect carrying the GPS signal from the antenna to the navigation receiver.", "gold_eccn": "9A991.d", "manufacturer": "Piper Aircraft", "source_url": "https://www.pilotshq.com/products/piper-aircraft-coax-gps-2-assembly-101918-003-oem-replacement", "source_type": "manufacturer_self_classification", "verified": true, "category": "9", "difficulty": "medium", "notes": "TIER C (PilotsHQ; human-visible). Quote: \"9A991.d\". HARD CASE: a GPS/avionics RF part classified as an aircraft component (9A991.d) rather than nav equipment (7A994). CAVEAT: distributor-templated default; cross-check vs OEM. verified=false."}
